What is Tableau? 
Tableau is a data visualization and business intelligence tool that helps you turn raw data into interactive charts, graphs, reports, and dashboards — without any coding.
Why is Tableau Used?
Tableau is popular because it:
Creates charts and dashboards quickly
Works with large datasets smoothly
Is completely drag-and-drop
Helps analyze data visually
Makes decision-making faster
Supports maps, forecasting, trends
Does not require programming
Where is Tableau Used?
Tableau is used in:
Banking
Retail
E-commerce
Healthcare
Marketing
Finance
Data Analytics
Business Reporting
HR Analytics
Companies use Tableau to understand performance and make decisions.
Tableau Products
Tableau Public – Free version for learning
Tableau Desktop – Professional version (advanced features)
Tableau Server – Used by companies to share dashboards internally
Tableau Cloud – Online platform to share dashboards
Tableau Prep – Data cleaning/ETL tool
What Tableau Can Do
Build charts (bar, line, pie, scatter, maps, etc.)
Create interactive dashboards
Add filters, highlights, actions
Use calculations
Create map visualizations
Build stories to present insights
Analyze trends and forecasts
